<subSubSection type="nomenclature">
<paragraph>[[ Peckoltia ]]</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="discussion">
<paragraph pageNumber="1">
Currently, 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:CAAEE496-AF6C-4F5B-AFDD-F2E8E6519E80" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Peckoltia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Peckoltia Miranda-Ribeiro 1912:7" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Peckoltia</taxonomicName>
is recognized in the subfamily Hypostominae, tribe Ancistrini of the Loricariidae (Armbruster, in press). It is considered a basal genus of the Ancistrini with no clear relationships to other taxa and it is likely that it may be synonymous with 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:2AC0D766-F761-4436-B6F4-395BBA997694" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Hemiancistrus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Hemiancistrus Bleeker 1862:2" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Hemiancistrus</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:CAAEE496-AF6C-4F5B-AFDD-F2E8E6519E80" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Peckoltia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Peckoltia Miranda-Ribeiro 1912:7" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Peckoltia</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:2AC0D766-F761-4436-B6F4-395BBA997694" class="Actinopterygii" family="Loricariidae" genus="Hemiancistrus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Hemiancistrus Bleeker 1862:2" order="Siluriformes" pageNumber="1" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Hemiancistrus</taxonomicName>
are not diagnosable from one another and neither genus is supported by synapomorphies.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
